git is a distributer version control 

using git we can practice tracking and managing cahnges of software code.

create a repository ....one repository create only one time using ------git init
----------------------------------------------------------------------------
git init
git status

Initilize git into your project folder



after that go to github url and create repository Ex: db_connection
after that copy the url of your github repository ie: clone address
------------------------------------------------------------------------------
git remote add origin https://github.com/shrutika-patil/db_connection.git

this commad add remote (github.com) reference to your repository with the name "origin"

----------------------------------------------------------------------------
git add <filename1> <filename2>
git add .

Stage your files for commit

----------------------------------------------------------------------
git commit -m "<commit msg>"
 
----------------------------------------------------------------------------
git push origin <brannch name> 

use this command we want to push the local branch to github remote
##### here we have to give user name 
#### here we have to give user password ----- insteted of password we use here github url token 

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
git checkout -b connection

using this command we create a new branch that is connection

---------------------------------------------------------------------
git checkout <branch> 
(any branch name which is existing on your repository)

using this command we jumb to the one branch to the another branch

